message:
Inlined methods that were extracted to use
@SuppressWarnings("unchecked"). That's now unnecessary after the
Serializable -> Parcelable switch

Better explain what "recreate an account" means and that it now resets
folder classes. Translations into every language K-9 speaks. (With help
from google translate and native speakers)

Simplify folder-skip logic when cleaning out folders deleted on the
server. (Note that we no longer delete the archive folder locally, even
if it's killed upstream)

extract out "should we notify" from "notify";

rather than calculating the number of pre-existing new messages for this
sync twice, do it once, a bit earlier.
